Class ArrayList<E>

java.lang.Object
utils.ArrayList<E>
Type Parameters:
E - the type of elements stored in this list
All Implemented Interfaces:
utils.List<E>
public abstract class ArrayList<E> extends Object implements utils.List<E>
A custom implementation of a dynamic array-based list. This abstract class provides a partial implementation of the List interface and supports basic operations such as adding, removing, retrieving, and searching elements.

This class uses an underlying array to store elements and dynamically expands its capacity when required to accommodate additional elements. Subclasses must implement any remaining abstract methods from the List interface.

  • Method Details

    • ensureCapacity

      protected void ensureCapacity()
      Ensures that the internal array has sufficient capacity to store additional elements. If the array is full, its capacity is doubled.

      Throws an OutOfMemoryError if the array reaches its maximum allowed size. renamed from ensureSpace for better handling
